sec.p:
Five new species of free living marine nematodes belonging to genus Parodontophora are described from intertidal areas of Fujian Province, East China Sea. P . aequiramus sp. nov. is identified by the amphid with the same length of dorsal branch and ventral branch, opisthocephalic setae arranged as ( 2 D- 1 V
) 2 , precloacal supplements and armilliths present; Parodontophora irregularis sp. nov. is characterized by arranged irregularly opisthocephalic setae, excretory pore near cephalic setae at the anterior part of buccal cavity and precloacal supplements present; Parodontophora huoshanensis sp. nov. can be distinguished by the amphid 0.77–0.83 times the length of the buccal cavity, opisthocephalic setae arranged as ( 2 D- 1 V
) 2 and precloacal supplements present; Parodontophora microseta sp. nov. is characterized by the amphid 1.71–2.1 times the length of the buccal cavity, opisthocephalic setae arranged as ( 1 D- 1 V
) 2 , precloacal supplements present and anterior gonad to the right and posterior gonad to the left of the intestine; Parodontophora paramicroseta sp. nov. is characterized by the amphid 1.35–1.5 times the length of the buccal cavity, opisthocephalic setae arranged as ( 1 D- 1 V
) 2 , precloacal supplements present and anterior gonad to the left and posterior gonad to the right of the intestine. A pictorial key to the valid species of Parodontophora Timm, 1963 is given.

Since then, more new species have been reported from both marine and fresh waters (
Gagarin & Nguyen 2006 ;
Gagarin & Thanh 2008 ;
Hourston & Warwick 2010 ;
Wu et al.2000 ;
Zhang 2005 ;
Zou 2000 ). Currently, 26 species are recognised for the genus Parodontophora Timm, 1963 (http://www.marinespecies.org/index.php and http:// nemys.ugent.be).

Undisturbed sediment samples were collected from coastal areas of Fujian Province, East China Sea, i.e., intertidal sandy beaches of Huoshan Island in Zhangzhou City; intertidal mudflat of Baihajiao Island and Fenglin mangrove mudflats in Xiamen City; mangrove mudflats in the estuary of Zhang River and Jiulong River in Zhangzhou City; mangrove mudflats in the estuary of Luoyang River in Quanzhou City; Wanwu mangrove mudflats in Ningde City (showed in
). Collected samples were fixed with 5 % formalin in filtered seawater. In laboratory, samples were stained with 0.1 % of rose Bengal for more than 24 hours. All meiofauna were extracted from the sediment through decantation and/or Ludox centrifugation (
Jonge & Bouwman 1977 ). Each sample was washed into a lined Petri dish and the meiofauna were sorted under a stereoscopic microscope (Nikon smz 800 ). Nematodes were transferred into a solution containing, by volume, 90 % freshwater, 5 % of the 95 % ethanol and 5 % of glycerol in a cavity block to let ethanol slowly evaporate and then mounted in glycerol on permanent slides (
Seinhorst 1959 ). The description was obtained under a differential interference contrast microscopy (Nikon 80 i
), and the morphology was draw via a camera lucida. All holotypes and paratypes were deposited in the Third Institute of Oceanography, State Oceanic Administration, Xiamen, China .

body.p:
Parodontophora aequiramus sp. nov. can easily differ from other species of Parodontophora in amphid with the same length of dorsal branch and ventral branch and V-shaped aperture with three small projections in distal end of the spicule. Although P . pacifica Allgén, 1947 and P . diegoensis Allgén, 1951 show almost equal amphid in published pictures, it differs from them in morphological difference of copulatory apparatus. P . repens Smolyanko & Belogurov, 1995 as an only species comes close to P . aequiramus sp. nov. in having armilliths in the structure of the buccal cavity and males have supplements, but we can easily distinguish them by the opisthocephalic setae arrangement (( 4 D- 1 V
) 2vs . ( 2 D- 1 V
) 2 ), the ratio of dorsal branch length of the amphid to the ventral branch length ( 0.5vs . 1.0), the size of renette cell ( 0.31–0.37vs . 0.12–0.19 ), the number of supplements ( 10 ind vs . about 16 ind), the length of supplement field ( 143 µm vs . 302–343 µm) and morphological difference of copulatory apparatus (
Table 2 ).

